#Linus install instructions

#Clone or copy the repo to the Linux machine:


git clone https://github.com/abogue77/POTA-Logger

cd POTA-Logger

#Make the installer executable:
chmod +x install.sh

#Run the installer:
./install.sh

#The script will:

Verify Python 3 is present
Auto-install python3-tk via apt, dnf, pacman, or zypper if needed
Copy hamlog.pyw to ~/.local/share/hamlog/
Create a hamlog launcher in ~/.local/bin/
Create a hamlog.desktop entry for the app menu
Create ~/HamLog/ for logs and config
If prompted about PATH (script will tell you), add this to ~/.bashrc:


export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
Then reload: source ~/.bashrc

Launch the app:


hamlog
